Calculate the Histogram of oriented gradients for images¶

In [3]:
img = cv2.imread(cars[1000])                        # BGR Image
img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)          # RGB Image
img1 = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_RGB2GRAY)        # Gray Image
features, hogImg = calculateHog(img1, vis = True)

f = plt.figure(figsize=(24, 8))
ax1 = f.add_subplot(1, 3, 1)
ax1.title.set_text('Original Image')
ax1.imshow(img)
ax2 = f.add_subplot(1, 3, 2)
ax2.title.set_text('HOG Image')
ax2.imshow(hogImg, cmap='gray')
ax3 = f.add_subplot(1, 3, 3)
ax3.title.set_text('HOG Features')
ax3.plot(features)

load the dataset and train the model¶

In [5]:
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = splitDataset(cars_data, notCars_data)
model = trainModel(x_train, y_train)
y_pred = predict(model, x_train)
accuracy = getAccuracy(y_train, y_pred)
print("train accuracy:", accuracy)
y_pred = predict(model, x_test)
accuracy = getAccuracy(y_test, y_pred)
print("test accuracy:", accuracy)

train accuracy: 1.0
test accuracy: 1.0

In [6]:

disp = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix = cm, display_labels = model.classes_)
